No matter what kind of shipping you choose, the following things will affect how much it costs:
<br><br>
<strong>Car size and weight:</strong> How big and heavy your car is affects how much it costs to ship. Most of the time, it costs more to move an SUV or <a href="https://rapidautoshipping.com/services/truck-shipping-service" target="_blank"><strong>truck</strong> </a>than it does to move a passenger.
<br><br>
<strong>Type of car:</strong> If you're shipping motorbikes or all-terrain vehicles (<a href="https://rapidautoshipping.com/blogs/atv-transport" target="_blank"><strong>ATVs</strong></a>), you'll pay less than the average, but if you're shipping recreational vehicles (RVs), you can expect to spend a lot.
<br><br>
<strong>Locations for pick-up and delivery:</strong> Shipping to and from cities will be cheaper than shipping to and from rural areas.
<br><br>
<strong>Condition of the car:</strong> Shipping is easier if the car can still be driven, so it costs less to ship a working car than a broken one.
<br><br>
<strong>Distance:</strong> Shipping costs are usually higher per mile, but the total price is lower when the distance is short.
<br><br>
<strong>Time of year:</strong> Moving a car is most expensive in January and the summer because that's when most people do it.
